Peter Dada A commercial motorcyclist also known as Okada rider, identified as Idowu Akomolafe and one Abiodun Olomiye reportedly drowned on Friday evening in Ondo State. While Akomolafe was found dead by the roadside at Ijoka area of Akure, the state capital on Saturday morning, Olomiye reportedly drowned when he went swimming in a river in Uso town in the Owo Local Government Area of Ondo State, on Friday evening. According to a source,  Akomolafe was said to have drowned during the heavy rainfall which led to flooding in Ijoka area on Friday. The source said that due to the rain, the road was flooded, which made it difficult for the Okada rider to make his way through. It was said that, he lost control of the bike and was swept away by the flood. When contacted the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Mr. Femi Joseph, confirmed the development and said the police was investigating the incidents. He said, “The corpse of the deceased had been recovered by the local swimmers in Uso, and he had been buried at the riverbank in line with the tradition of the town.” Copyright PUNCH.
